Reasoning: The paper deals with the intersection of regular languages and combinatorial problems, which is a topic in formal language theory (cs.FL) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The connection between automata theory and combinatorial problems also falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper discusses the decidability of the intreg-problem, which is related to the decidability of regular languages, making it relevant to the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). Finally, the discussion of different encoding-schemes and alphabet sizes touches upon information theory (cs.IT).
